Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the
@green pepper{1}(halved and deseeded) and remove the core and seeds. Slice
into thin strips. Halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{about 15}. Peel and grate the
@garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the
@flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a good glug of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat.
Pop the onion and pepper into the pan. Mix well then leave to cook until
beginning to colour and soften, stirring occasionally, ~{5-7%minutes}. Once
soft, stir in the garlic, @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}, @tomato puree{30%g}
and a pinch of @chilli flakes{pinch} to taste (careful, they're hot!). Stir, then
cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pop the smoked fish mix into the pan along with the @water{300%ml} for the stew,
@?sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}
to taste. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat, cover with a #lid{} and
gently simmer for ~{25-30%minutes}, until the tomatoes have broken down and the
sauce has thickened slightly. Stir occasionally. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

== Couscous ==

In the meantime, put the @couscous{150%g}, one-quarter of the chopped parsley
and the @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp} in a #mixing bowl{}. From your kettle
pour the boiling @water for the couscous{300%ml} into the bowl, stir to dissolve
the stock powder, then cover tightly with #clingfilm{} and leave to the side
for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Parsley Dressing ==

Put the remaining parsley into a #small bowl{} and stir in the
@olive oil{2%tbsp}, season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of
@ground black pepper{}. Set aside.

== Finishing ==

When the stew has about ~{5%minutes} left, gently stir in the
@smoked fish mix{215%g}. Return the lid to the pan and continue to simmer for
~{4-5%minutes} until the fish is cooked.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the fish is cooked taste and add more salt and pepper if required. Fluff up
the couscous with a #fork{}, then divide between bowls with the fish stew
spooned over. Finish with a drizzle of the parsley oil. Tuck in!